      },
      "date": "2013-03-27 05:39:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIt seems to take forever to see ZFS results from Autotest; the patch passed my local testing, however.  I think it is ready for reviews.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ae5c084d778f111740d1b82c3e821b1931343a36",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 141,
        "name": "Li Wei",
        "email": "wei.g.li@intel.com",
        "username": "liwei",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-03-27 05:43:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOne idea back in the Orion days is to rewrite some of the tests that depends on free space comparisons to verify existences of certain objects with facilities like those provided by this patch.  They could mount the back end file system directly and check what they want to verify.  Also, mounting and accessing ZFS directly, although infrequent, would give us a little bit of verification that our ZFS-based targets are somewhat ZPL-compatible.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
